cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

The paper proposes an approach for automatic construction of a binary classifier based on LSTM-RNNs for detection of a vehicle passage through a checkpoint. This involves time-series modeling and prediction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The input to the classifier is multidimensional signals of various sensors, which suggests the use of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The use of RNNs also indicates the possibility of neural networks (cs.NE) being involved. Finally, the paper deals with the detection of a vehicle passage, which could be considered a security-related issue, and hence could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
